33415|"_The hall of EARTH-SPIRIT_, Act IV, _feebly lighted by an oil lamp on"|FALSE
33415|"the centre table. Even this is dimmed by a heavy shade. Lulu's"|FALSE
33415|"picture is gone from the easel, which still stands by the foot of the"|FALSE
33415|"stairs. The fire-screen and the chair by the ottoman are gone too."|FALSE
33415|"Down left is a small tea-table, with a coffee-pot and a cup of black"|FALSE
33415|"coffee on it, and an arm-chair next it._"|FALSE
33415|"_In this chair, deep in cushions, with a plaid shawl over her knees,"|FALSE
33415|"sits Countess Geschwitz in a tight black dress. Rodrigo, clad as a"|FALSE
33415|"servant, sits on the ottoman. At the rear, Alva Schön is walking up"|FALSE
33415|"and down before the entrance door._"|FALSE
33415|"RODRIGO. He lets people wait for him as if he were a concert"|FALSE
33415|"conductor!"|FALSE
33415|"GESCHWITZ. I beg of you, don't speak!"|FALSE
33415|"RODRIGO. Hold my tongue, with a head as full of thoughts as mine"|FALSE
33415|"is!--I absolutely can't believe she's changed so awfully much to her"|FALSE
33415|"advantage there!"|FALSE
33415|"GESCHWITZ. She is more glorious to look at than I have ever seen her!"|FALSE
33415|"RODRIGO. God preserve me from founding my life-happiness on your"|FALSE
33415|"taste and judgment! If the sickness has hit her as it has you, I'm"|FALSE
33415|"smashed and thru! You're leaving the contagious ward like an"|FALSE
33415|"acrobat-lady who's had an accident after giving herself up to art."|FALSE
33415|"You can scarcely blow your nose any more. First you need a"|FALSE
33415|"quarter-hour to sort your fingers, and then you have to be mighty"|FALSE
33415|"careful not to break off the tip."|FALSE
33415|"GESCHWITZ. What puts *us* under the ground gives *her* health and"|FALSE
33415|"strength again."|FALSE
33415|"RODRIGO. That's all right and fine enough. But I don't think I'll be"|FALSE
33415|"travelling off with her this evening."|FALSE
33415|"GESCHWITZ. You will let your bride journey all alone, after all?"|FALSE
33415|"RODRIGO. In the first place, the old fellow's going with her to"|FALSE
33415|"protect her in case anything serious--. My escort could only be"|FALSE
33415|"suspicious. And secondly, I must wait here till my costumes are"|FALSE
33415|"ready. I'll get across the frontier soon enough alright,--and I hope"|FALSE
33415|"in the meantime she'll put on a little embonpoint, too. Then we'll"|FALSE
33415|"get married, provided I can present her before a respectable public."|FALSE
33415|"I love the practical in a woman: what theories they make up for"|FALSE
33415|"themselves are all the same to me. Aren't they to you too, doctor?"|FALSE
33415|"ALVA. I haven't heard what you were saying."|FALSE
33415|"RODRIGO. I'd never have got my person mixed up in this plot if she"|FALSE
33415|"hadn't kept tickling my bare pate, before her sentence. If only she"|FALSE
33415|"doesn't start doing too much as soon as she's out of Germany! I'd"|FALSE
33415|"like best to take her to London for six months, and let her fill up"|FALSE
33415|"on plum-cakes. In London one expands just from the sea air. And then,"|FALSE
33415|"too, in London one doesn't feel with every swallow of beer as if the"|FALSE
33415|"hand of fate were at one's throat."|FALSE
33415|"ALVA. I've been asking myself for a week whether a person who'd been"|FALSE
33415|"sentenced to prison could still be made to go as the chief figure in"|FALSE
33415|"a modern drama."|FALSE
33415|"GESCHWITZ. If the man would only come, now!"|FALSE
33415|"RODRIGO. I've still got to redeem my properties out of the pawn-shop"|FALSE
33415|"here, too. Six hundred kilos of the best iron. The baggage-rate on"|FALSE
33415|"'em is always three times as much as my own ticket, so that the whole"|FALSE
33415|"junket isn't worth a trowser's button. When I went into the pawn-shop"|FALSE
33415|"with 'em, dripping with sweat, they asked me if the things were"|FALSE
33415|"genuine!--I'd have really done better to have had the costumes made"|FALSE
33415|"abroad. In Paris, for instance, they see at the first glance where"|FALSE
33415|"one's best points are, and bravely lay them bare. But you can't learn"|FALSE
33415|"that with bow-legs; it's got to be studied on classically shaped"|FALSE
33415|"people. In this country they're as scared of naked skin as they are"|FALSE
33415|"abroad of dynamite bombs. A couple of years ago I was fined fifty"|FALSE
33415|"marks at the Alhambra Theater, because people could see I had a few"|FALSE
33415|"hairs on my chest, not enough to make a respectable tooth-brush! But"|FALSE
33415|"the Fine Arts Minister opined that the little school-girls might lose"|FALSE
33415|"their joy in knitting stockings because of it; and since then I have"|FALSE
33415|"myself shaved once a month."|FALSE
33415|"ALVA. If I didn't need every bit of my creative power now for the"|FALSE
33415|"\"World-conqueror,\" I might like to test the problem and see what"|FALSE
33415|"could be done with it. That's the curse of our young literature:"|FALSE
33415|"we're so much too literary. We know only such questions and problems"|FALSE
33415|"as come up among writers and cultured people. We cannot see beyond"|FALSE
33415|"the limits of our own professional interests. In order to get back on"|FALSE
33415|"the trail of a great and powerful art we must move as much as"|FALSE
33415|"possible among men who've never read a book in their lives, whom the"|FALSE
33415|"simplest animal instincts direct in all they do. I've tried already,"|FALSE
33415|"with all my might, to work according to those principles--in my"|FALSE
33415|"\"Earth-spirit.\" The woman who was my model for the chief figure in"|FALSE
33415|"that, breathes to-day--and has for a year--behind barred windows; and"|FALSE
33415|"on that account for some incomprehensible reason the play was only"|FALSE
33415|"brought to performance by the Society for Free Literature. As long as"|FALSE
33415|"my father was alive, all the stages of Germany stood open to my"|FALSE
33415|"creations. That has been vastly changed."|FALSE
33415|"RODRIGO. I've had a pair of tights made of the tenderest blue-green."|FALSE
33415|"If *they* don't make a success abroad, I'll sell mouse-traps! The"|FALSE
33415|"trunks are so delicate I can't sit on the edge of a table in 'em. The"|FALSE
33415|"only thing that will disturb the good impression is my awful bald"|FALSE
33415|"head, which I owe to my active participation in this great"|FALSE
33415|"conspiracy. To lie in the hospital in perfect health for three months"|FALSE
33415|"would make a fat pig of the most run-down old hobo. Since coming out"|FALSE
33415|"I've fed on nothing but Karlsbad pills. Day and night I have"|FALSE
33415|"orchestra rehearsals in my intestines. I'll be so washed out before I"|FALSE
