33415|"KUNGU POTI. Doesn't matter. (_Drinks._) Brandy! Lots of it!"|FALSE
33415|"LULU. You're a nice-looking young man."|FALSE
33415|"KUNGU POTI. My father's the emperor of Uahubee. I've got six wives"|FALSE
33415|"here, two Spanish, two English, two French. Well--I don't like my"|FALSE
33415|"wives. Always I must take a bath, take a bath, take a bath...."|FALSE
33415|"LULU. How much will you give me?"|FALSE
33415|"KUNGU POTI. Gold! Trust me, you shall have gold! One gold-piece. I"|FALSE
33415|"always give gold-pieces."|FALSE
33415|"LULU. You can give it to me later, but show it to me."|FALSE
33415|"KUNGU POTI. I never pay beforehand."|FALSE
33415|"LULU. But you can show it to me, thoh!"|FALSE
33415|"KUNGU POTI. Don't understand, don't understand! Come,"|FALSE
33415|"Ragapsishimulara! (_Seizing Lulu round the waist._) Come on!"|FALSE
33415|"LULU. (_Defending herself with all her strength._) Let me be! Let me"|FALSE
33415|"be! (_Alva, who has risen painfully from his couch, sneaks up to"|FALSE
33415|"Kungu Poti from behind and pulls him back by the collar._)"|FALSE
33415|"KUNGU POTI. (_Whirling round._) Oh! Oh! This is a murder-hole! Come,"|FALSE
33415|"my friend, I'll put you to sleep! (_Strikes him over the head with a"|FALSE
33415|"loaded cane. Alva groans and falls in a heap._) Here's a"|FALSE
33415|"sleeping-draught! Here's opium for you! Sweet dreams to you! Sweet"|FALSE
33415|"dreams! (_Then he gives Lulu a kiss; pointing to Alva._) He dreams of"|FALSE
33415|"you, Ragapsishimulara! Sweet dreams! (_Rushing to the door._) Here's"|FALSE
33415|"the door!! (_Exit._)"|FALSE
33415|"LULU. But I'll not stay here?!--Who can stand it here now!--Rather"|FALSE
33415|"down onto the street! (_Exit. Schigolch comes out._)"|FALSE
33415|"SCHIGOLCH.--Blood!--Alva!--He's got to be put away somewhere."|FALSE
33415|"Hop!--Or else our friends 'll get a shock from him--Alva! Alva!--He"|FALSE
33415|"that isn't quite clear about it--! One thing or t'other; or it'll"|FALSE
33415|"soon be too late! I'll give him legs! (_Strikes a match and sticks it"|FALSE
33415|"into Alva's collar...._) He will have his rest. But no one sleeps"|FALSE
33415|"here.--(_Drags him by the head into Lulu's room. Returning, he tries"|FALSE
33415|"to turn up the light._) It'll be time for me, too, right soon now, or"|FALSE
33415|"they'll get no more Christmas puddings down there in the tavern. God"|FALSE
33415|"knows when she'll be coming back from her pleasure tour! (_Fixing an"|FALSE
33415|"eye on Lulu's picture._) She doesn't understand business! She can't"|FALSE
33415|"live off love, because her life is love.--There she comes. I'll just"|FALSE
33415|"talk straight to her once--(_Countess Geschwitz enters._) ... If you"|FALSE
33415|"want to lodge with us to-night, kindly take a little care that"|FALSE
33415|"nothing is stolen here."|FALSE
33415|"GESCHWITZ. How dark it is here!"|FALSE
33415|"SCHIGOLCH. It gets much darker than this.--The doctor's already gone"|FALSE
33415|"to rest."|FALSE
33415|"GESCHWITZ. She sent me ahead."|FALSE
33415|"SCHIGOLCH. That was sensible.--If anyone asks for me, I'm sitting"|FALSE
33415|"downstairs in the pub."|FALSE
33415|"GESCHWITZ. (_After he has gone._) I will sit behind the door. I will"|FALSE
33415|"look on at everything and not quiver an eye-lash. (_Sits on the"|FALSE
33415|"broken chair._) Men and women don't know themselves--they know not"|FALSE
33415|"what they are. Only one who is neither man nor woman knows them."|FALSE
33415|"Every word they say is untrue, a lie. And they do not know it, for"|FALSE
33415|"they are to-day so and to-morrow so, according as they have eaten,"|FALSE
33415|"drunk, and loved, or not. Only the body remains for a time what it"|FALSE
33415|"is, and only the children have reason. The men and women are like the"|FALSE
33415|"animals: none knows what it does. When they are happiest they bewail"|FALSE
33415|"themselves and groan, and in their deepest misery they rejoice over"|FALSE
33415|"every tiny morsel. It is strange how hunger takes from men and women"|FALSE
33415|"the strength to withstand misfortune. But when they have fed full"|FALSE
33415|"they make this world a torture-chamber, they throw away their lives"|FALSE
33415|"to satisfy a whim, a mood. Have there ever once been men and women to"|FALSE
33415|"whom love brought happiness? And what is their happiness, save that"|FALSE
33415|"they sleep better and can forget it all? My God, I thank thee that"|FALSE
33415|"thou hast not made me as these. I am not man nor woman. My body has"|FALSE
33415|"nothing common with their bodies. Have I a human soul? Tortured"|FALSE
33415|"humanity has a little narrow heart; but I know I deserve nothing when"|FALSE
33415|"I resign all, sacrifice all.... (_Lulu opens the door, and Dr. Hilti"|FALSE
33415|"enters. Geschwitz, unnoticed, remains motionless by the door._)"|FALSE
33415|"LULU. (_Gaily._) Come right in! Come!--you'll stay with me all night?"|FALSE
33415|"DR. HILTI. (_His accent is very broad and flat._) But I have no more"|FALSE
33415|"than five shillings on me. I never take more than that when I go out."|FALSE
33415|"LULU. That's enough, because it's you! You have such faithful eyes!"|FALSE
33415|"Come, give me a kiss! (_Dr. Hilti begins to swear, in the broadest"|FALSE
33415|"north-country vowels._) Please, don't say that."|FALSE
33415|"DR. HILTI. By the de'il, 'tis the first time I've e'er gone with a"|FALSE
33415|"girrl! You can believe me. Mass, I hadn't thought it would be like"|FALSE
33415|"this!"|FALSE
33415|"LULU. Are you married?"|FALSE
33415|"DR. HILTI. Heaven and Hail, why do you think I am married?--No, I'm a"|FALSE
33415|"tutor; I read philosophy at the University. The truth is, I come of a"|FALSE
33415|"very old country family. As a student, I got just two shillings"|FALSE
33415|"pocket-money, and I could make better use of that than for girrls!"|FALSE
33415|"LULU. So you have never been with a woman?"|FALSE
33415|"DR. HILTI. Just so, yes! But I want it now. I got engaged this"|FALSE
33415|"evening to a country-woman of mine. She's a governess here."|FALSE
33415|"LULU. Is she pretty?"|FALSE
33415|"DR. HILTI. Yaw, she's got a hundred thousand.--I am very eager, as it"|FALSE
33415|"seems to me...."|FALSE
33415|"LULU. (_Tossing back her hair._) I *am* in luck! (_Takes the lamp._)"|FALSE
33415|"Well, if you please, Mr. Tutor? (_They go into her room. Geschwitz"|FALSE
33415|"draws a small black revolver from her pocket and sets it to her"|FALSE
33415|"forehead._)"|FALSE
33415|"GESCHWITZ.--Come, come,--beloved! (_Dr. Hilti tears open the door"|FALSE
33415|"again.--_)"|FALSE
33415|"DR. HILTI. (_Plunging in._) Insane seraphs! Some one's lying in"|FALSE
33415|"there!"|FALSE
33415|"LULU. (_Lamp in hand, holds him by the sleeve._) Stay with me!"|FALSE
33415|"DR. HILTI. A dead man! A corpse!"|FALSE
33415|"LULU. Stay with me! Stay with me!"|FALSE
33415|"DR. HILTI. (_Tearing away._) A corpse is lying in there! Horrors!"|FALSE
33415|"Hail! Heaven!"|FALSE
33415|"LULU. Stay with me!"|FALSE
33415|"DR. HILTI. Where d's it go out? (_Sees Geschwitz._) And there is the"|FALSE
33415|"devil!"|FALSE
33415|"LULU. Please, stop, stay!"|FALSE
33415|"DR. HILTI. Devil, devilled devilry!--Oh, thou eternal--(_Exit._)"|FALSE
33415|"LULU. (_Rushing after him._) Stop! Stop!"|FALSE
33415|"GESCHWITZ. (_Alone, lets the revolver sink._) Better, hang! If she"|FALSE
33415|"sees me lie in my blood to-day she'll not weep a tear for me! I have"|FALSE
33415|"always been to her but the docile tool that could be used for the"|FALSE
33415|"heaviest labor. From the first day she has abhorred me from the"|FALSE
33415|"depths of her soul.--Shall I not rather jump from the bridge? Which"|FALSE
33415|"could be colder, the water or her heart? I would dream till I was"|FALSE
33415|"drowned.--Better, hang!-- --Stab?--Hm, there would be no use in"|FALSE
33415|"that-- --How often have I dreamt that she kissed me! But a minute"|FALSE
33415|"more; an owl knocks there at the window, and I wake up.-- --Better,"|FALSE
33415|"hang! Not water; water is too clean for me. (_Starting up._)"|FALSE
33415|"There!--There! There it is!--Quick now, before she comes! (_Takes the"|FALSE
33415|"plaid-straps from the wall, climbs on the chair, fastens them to a"|FALSE
33415|"hook in the door-post, puts her head thru them, kicks the chair away,"|FALSE
33415|"and falls to the ground._) Accursed life!--Accursed life!--Could it"|FALSE
33415|"be before me still??--Let me speak just once to thy heart, my angel!"|FALSE
33415|"But thou art cold!--I am not to go yet! Perhaps I am even to have"|FALSE
33415|"been happy once.--Listen to him, Lulu! I am not to go yet! (_She"|FALSE
33415|"drags herself before Lulu's picture, sinks to her knees and folds her"|FALSE
33415|"hands._) My adoréd angel! My love! My star!--Have mercy upon me, pity"|FALSE
33415|"me, pity me, pity me!"|FALSE
33415|"(_Lulu opens the door, and Jack enters--a thick-set man of elastic"|FALSE
33415|"movements, with a pale face, inflamed eyes, arched and heavy brows, a"|FALSE
33415|"drooping mustache, thin imperial and shaggy whiskers, and fiery red"|FALSE
33415|"hands with gnawed nails. His eyes are fixed on the ground. He wears a"|FALSE
33415|"dark overcoat and a little round felt hat. Entering, he notices"|FALSE
33415|"Geschwitz._)"|FALSE
33415|"JACK. Who is that?"|FALSE
33415|"LULU. That's my sister. She's crazy. I don't know how to get rid of"|FALSE
33415|"her."|FALSE
33415|"JACK. Your mouth looks beautiful."|FALSE
33415|"LULU. It's my mother's."|FALSE
33415|"JACK. Looks like it. How much do you want? I haven't got much money."|FALSE
33415|"LULU. Won't you spend the night with me here?"|FALSE
33415|"JACK. No, haven't got the time. I must get home."|FALSE
33415|"LULU. You can tell them at home to-morrow that you missed the last"|FALSE
33415|"'bus and spent the night with a friend."|FALSE
33415|"JACK. How much do you want?"|FALSE
33415|"LULU. I'm not after lumps of gold, but, well, a little something."|FALSE
33415|"JACK. (_Turning._) Good night! Good night!"|FALSE
33415|"LULU. (_Holds him back._) No, no! Stay, for God's sake!"|FALSE
33415|"JACK. (_Goes past Geschwitz and opens the cubicle._) Why should I"|FALSE
33415|"stay here till morning? Sounds suspicious! When I'm asleep they'll"|FALSE
33415|"turn my pockets out."|FALSE
33415|"LULU. No, I won't do that! No one will! Don't go away again for that!"|FALSE
33415|"I beg you!"|FALSE
33415|"JACK. How much do you want?"|FALSE
33415|"LULU. Then give me the half of what I said!"|FALSE
33415|"JACK. No, that's too much. You don't seem to have been at this long?"|FALSE
33415|"LULU. To-day is the first time. (_She jerks back Geschwitz, on her"|FALSE
33415|"knees still, half turned toward Jack, by the straps around her"|FALSE
33415|"neck._) Lie down and be quiet!"|FALSE
33415|"JACK. Let her alone! She isn't your sister. She is in love with you."|FALSE
33415|"(_Strokes Geschwitz's head like a dog's._) Poor beast!"|FALSE
33415|"LULU. Why do you stare at me so all at once?"|FALSE
33415|"JACK. I got your measure by the way you walked. I said to myself:"|FALSE
33415|"That girl must have a well-built body."|FALSE
33415|"LULU. How can you see things like that?"|FALSE
33415|"JACK. I even saw that you had a pretty mouth. But I've only got a"|FALSE
33415|"florin on me."|FALSE
33415|"LULU. Well, what difference does that make! Just give that to me!"|FALSE
33415|"JACK. But you'll have to give me half back, so I can take the 'bus"|FALSE
33415|"to-morrow morning."|FALSE
33415|"LULU. I have nothing on me."|FALSE
33415|"JACK. Just look, thoh. Hunt thru your pockets!--Well, what's that?"|FALSE
33415|"Let's see it!"|FALSE
33415|"LULU. (_Showing him._) That's all I have."|FALSE
33415|"JACK. Give it to me!"|FALSE
33415|"LULU. I'll change it to-morrow, and then give you half."|FALSE
33415|"JACK. No, give it all to me."|FALSE
33415|"LULU. (_Giving it._) In God's name! But now you come! (_Takes up the"|FALSE
33415|"lamp._)"|FALSE
33415|"JACK. We need no light. The moon's out."|FALSE
33415|"LULU. (_Puts the lamp down._) As you say. (_She falls on his neck._)"|FALSE
33415|"I won't harm you at all! I love you so! Don't let me beg you any"|FALSE
33415|"longer!"|FALSE
33415|"JACK. Alright; I'm with you. (_Follows her into the cubby-hole. The"|FALSE
33415|"lamp goes out. On the floor under the two sky-lights appear two vivid"|FALSE
33415|"squares of moonlight. Everything in the room is clearly seen._)"|FALSE
33415|"GESCHWITZ. (_As in a dream._) This is the last evening I shall spend"|FALSE
33415|"with these people. I'm going back to Germany. My mother'll send me"|FALSE
33415|"the money. I'll go to a university. I must fight for woman's rights;"|FALSE
33415|"study law.... (_Lulu shrieks, and tears open the door._)"|FALSE
33415|"LULU. (_Barefoot, in chemise and petticoat, holding the door shut"|FALSE
33415|"behind her._) Help!"|FALSE
33415|"GESCHWITZ. (_Rushes to the door, draws her revolver, and pushing Lulu"|FALSE
33415|"aside, aims it at the door. As Lulu again cries \"Help!\"_) Let go!"|FALSE
33415|"(_Jack, bent double, tears open the door from inside, and runs a"|FALSE
33415|"knife into Geschwitz's body. She fires one shot, at the roof, and"|FALSE
33415|"falls with suppressed crying, crumpling up. Jack tears her revolver"|FALSE
33415|"from her and throws himself against the exit-door._)"|FALSE
33415|"JACK. God damn! I never saw a prettier mouth! (_Sweat drips from his"|FALSE
33415|"hairy face. His hands are bloody. He pants, gasping violently, and"|FALSE
33415|"stares at the floor with eyes popping out of his head. Lulu,"|FALSE
33415|"trembling in every limb, looks wildly round. Suddenly she seizes the"|FALSE
33415|"bottle, smashes it on the table, and with the broken neck in her hand"|FALSE
33415|"rushes upon Jack. He swings up his right foot and throws her onto her"|FALSE
33415|"back. Then he lifts her up._)"|FALSE
33415|"LULU. No, no!--Mercy!--Murder!--Police! Police!"|FALSE
33415|"JACK. Be still. You'll never get away from me again. (_Carries her"|FALSE
33415|"in._)"|FALSE
33415|"LULU. (_Within, right._) No!--No!--No!-- --Ah!--Ah!..."|FALSE
33415|"(_After a pause, Jack re-enters. He puts the bowl on the table._)"|FALSE
33415|"JACK. That *was* a piece of work! (_Washing his hands._) I *am* a"|FALSE
33415|"damned lucky chap! (_Looks round for a towel._) Not even a towel,"|FALSE
33415|"these folks here! Hell of a wretched hole! (_He dries his hands on"|FALSE
33415|"Geschwitz's petticoat._) This invert is safe enough from me! (_To"|FALSE
33415|"her._) It'll soon be all up with you, too. (_Exit._)"|FALSE
33415|"GESCHWITZ. (_Alone._) Lulu!--My angel!--Let me see thee once more! I"|FALSE
33415|"am near thee--stay near thee--forever! (_Her elbows give way._) O"|FALSE
33415|"cursed--!! (_Dies._)"|FALSE
33415|"  CURTAIN."|FALSE
